    <item>
      <title>Authorization Server in Spring Boot 3.1</title>
      <link>https://dashaun.dev/blog/authorization-server-3-1-1.html</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 4 Jul 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">blog/authorization-server-3-1-1.html</guid>
      	<description>
	&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The site source code is available on [GitHub](&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/dashaun-dev&quot; class=&quot;bare&quot;&gt;https://github.com/dashaun-dev&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, there is a Spring Cloud Gateway deployed, and it sits in front of this JBake website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, I added &lt;a href=&quot;https://spring.io/projects/spring-authorization-server&quot;&gt;Spring Authorization Server&lt;/a&gt; and just setup an InMemoryUserDetailsManager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This setup is very similar to what Josh Long and Steve Riesenberg did in their video &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7zm3mxaAFWk&quot;&gt;Going Full OAuth with the new Spring Authorization Server in Spring Boot 3.1&lt;/a&gt;.  I just took it a little further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ulist&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I made everything publicly accessible by using a Cloudflare Argo Tunnel&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I pushed it all to production&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the moment (July 4th, 2023), I have these services deployed to KNative 1.10, on Docker Desktop, running on my Mac dev machine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
	</description>
